              <h3><a name="qlcal-r_0.0.6"><b>qlcal 0.0.6 on CRAN: More updates from QuantLib</b></a></h3>

	       
<p>The sixth release of the still new-ish <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/qlcal-r.html">qlcal</a> package
arrivied at <a href="https://cran.r-project.org">CRAN</a> today.</p>
<p><a href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/qlcal-r.html">qlcal</a>
delivers the calendaring parts of <a
href="https://www.quantlib.org">QuantLib</a>. It is provided (for the R
package) as a set of included files, so the package is self-contained
and does not depend on an external <a
href="https://www.quantlib.org">QuantLib</a> library (which can be
demanding to build). <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/qlcal-r.html">qlcal</a> covers
over sixty country / market calendars and can compute holiday lists, its
complement (<em>i.e.</em> business day lists) and much more.</p>
<p>This release brings updates to a few calendars which happened since
the QuantLib 1.30 release, and also updates a several of the (few)
non-calendaring functions.</p>
<blockquote>
<h4 id="changes-in-version-0.0.6-2023-05-24">Changes in version 0.0.6
(2023-05-24)</h4>
<ul>
<li><p>Several calendars (India, Singapore, South Africa, South Korea)
updated with post-QuantLib 1.3.0 changes (Sebastian Schmidt in <a
href="https://github.com/qlcal/qlcal-r/pull/6">#6</a>)</p></li>
<li><p>Three now-used scheduled files were removed (Dirk in <a
href="https://github.com/qlcal/qlcal-r/pull/7">#7</a>))</p></li>
<li><p>A number of non-calendaring files used were synchronised with the
current QuantLib repo (Dirk in <a
href="https://github.com/qlcal/qlcal-r/pull/8">#8</a>)</p></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>Last release, we also added a quick little demo using
<code>xts</code> to column-bind calendars produced from each of the
different US sub-calendars. This is a slightly updated version of the
sketch <a
href="https://mastodon.social/@eddelbuettel/110204785778738939">we
tooted a few days ago</a>. The output now is</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="sc">&gt;</span> <span class="fu">print</span>(<span class="fu">Reduce</span>(cbind, <span class="fu">Map</span>(makeHol, cals)))</span>
