              <h3><a name="pkgKitten_0.2.3"><b>pkgKitten 0.2.3 on CRAN: Minor Update</b></a></h3>

	       
<p><img alt="kitten"
     style="float:left;margin:10px 30px 10px 0;"
     width="200" 
     src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-rUsj-zdsAls/UY81UzuYHsI/AAAAAAAAAJA/QMiiNxYuvdI/s1600/burmilla-kitten.png"/></p>
<p>A new release 0.2.3 of <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/pkgkitten.html">pkgKitten</a>
arrived on <a href="https://cran.r-project.org">CRAN</a> earlier, and
will be uploaded to Debian. <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/pkgkitten.html">pkgKitten</a>
makes it simple to create new R packages via a simple function
invocation. A wrapper <code>kitten.r</code> exists in the <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/littler.html">littler</a>
package to make it even easier.</p>
<p>This release improves the created ‘Description:’, and updated some of
the continuous integration.</p>
<blockquote>
<h4 id="changes-in-version-0.2.3-2023-03-11">Changes in version 0.2.3
(2023-03-11)</h4>
<ul>
<li><p>Small improvement to generated Description: field and
Title:</p></li>
<li><p>Maintenance for continuous integration setup</p></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>More details about the package are at the <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/pkgkitten.html">pkgKitten
webpage</a>, the <a
href="https://eddelbuettel.github.io/pkgkitten">pkgKitten docs site</a>,
and the <a href="https://github.com/eddelbuettel/pkgkitten">pkgKitten
GitHub repo</a>.</p>
<p>Courtesy of my <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/cranberries/">CRANberries</a> site,
there is also a diffstat report for <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/cranberries/2023/03/11#pkgKitten_0.2.3">this
release</a>.</p>
<p>If you like this or other open-source work I do, you can now <a
href="https://github.com/sponsors/eddelbuettel">sponsor me at
GitHub</a>.</p>
