              <h3><a name="rcppgsl_0.3.13"><b>RcppGSL 0.3.13 on CRAN: Mandated Update</b></a></h3>

	       
<p>A new release 0.3.13 of <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/rcpp.gsl.html">RcppGSL</a> is
now on <a href="htts://cran.r-project.org">CRAN</a>. The <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/rcpp.gsl.html">RcppGSL</a>
package provides an interface from <a
href="https://www.r-project.org">R</a> to the <a
href="https://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/">GNU GSL</a> by relying on the
<a href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/rcpp.html">Rcpp</a>
package.</p>
<p>This release contains one change (made at the request of a CRAN email
in light of possible future changes for C standard C17 and then C23) and
removes a compiler-check from <code>configure.ac</code>. It is both a
fair point as our <code>src/Makevars</code> does not actually set a
compiler yet also a little … marginal?</p>
<p>The NEWS entry follows:</p>
<blockquote>
<h4 id="changes-in-version-0.3.13-2023-01-12">Changes in version 0.3.13
(2023-01-12)</h4>
<ul>
<li>Remove 'AC_PROG_CC' from 'configure.ac' per CRAN wish</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>Courtesy of <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/cranberries/">CRANberries</a>, a
summary of changes in <a
href="https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/cranberries/2023/01/12#RcppGSL_0.3.13">the
most recent release</a> is also available.</p>
<p>More information is on the <a
