              <h3><a name="linl_0.0.5"><b>linl 0.0.5 on CRAN: Extended Background Support</b></a></h3>

	       
<p>A new release of our <a
href="http://cloud.r-project.org/package=linl">linl package</a> for
writing LaTeX letters with (R)markdown is now on CRAN. <a
href="http://cloud.r-project.org/package=linl">linl</a> makes it easy to
write letters in markdown, with some extra bells and whistles thanks to
some cleverness chiefly by <a
href="http://aaronwolen.com/">Aaron</a>.</p>
<p>This version add extended header and footer placement support thanks
to an included copy of <code>wallpaper.sty</code> as added in a nice PR
by <a href="https://github.com/enchufa2">Iñaki</a>. As the previous
release was well over three years ago, we also enhanced continuous
integration in the process. The <a
href="https://github.com/eddelbuettel/linl">repository README.md</a>
shows some screenshots of input and output files.</p>
<p>The NEWS entry follows:</p>
<blockquote>
<h4 id="changes-in-linl-version-0.0.5-2023-01-11">Changes in linl
version 0.0.5 (2023-01-11)</h4>
<ul>
<li><p>Several updates to continuous integration and testing</p></li>
<li><p>Enhanced placment functionality for images in header and footer
via <code>wallpaper.sty</code> and new x and y offset variable (Iñaki
Ucar in <a
href="https://github.com/eddelbuettel/linl/pull/30">#30</a>)</p></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>Courtesy of <a
href="http://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/cranberries/">CRANberries</a>, there
is a comparison to <a
href="http://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/cranberries/2023/01/11#linl_0.0.5">the
previous release</a>. More information is on the <a
href="http://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/linl.html">linl</a> page. For
questions or comments use the <a
href="https://github.com/eddelbuettel/linl/issues">issue tracker</a> off
the <a href="https://github.com/eddelbuettel/linl">GitHub repo</a>.</p>
<p>If you like this or other open-source work I do, you can now <a
href="https://github.com/sponsors/eddelbuettel">sponsor me at
GitHub</a>.</p>
